Limpopo police have nabbed a 51 -year -old teacher who is accused of raping a 14 – year -old pupil. According to the police, the teacher allegedly raped the student in his car after giving her a lift home after school. “The suspect will appear before the Ritavi Magistrate ‘s Court on Tuesday on a charge of rape,” said SAPS spokesperson LT. Colonel Moatshe’ Ngoepe . Provincial Commissioner LT. General Nneke Ledwaba condemned the incident saying “child safety must be everybody’s bussiness within our society especially people in the calibre of t eachers who are expected play a secondary parental role to any child .” Recently allegations that more than 80 pupils ha d been sexually molested by a school security guard at the AB Xuma Primary School in Soweto has sent shock waves. Meanwhile, Gauteng education MEC Panyaza Lesufi is on Monday visiting another school in Mamelodi, Pretoria today folowing allegations of rape of a 17-year-old pupil by a scholar patroller. -TNA Reporter